## First moves

```bash
# Discover + fingerprint the whole segment
./scan-lab.sh

# Metasploit recon (loads recon.rc)
msfconsole -q -r recon.rc

# Capture the segment in Wireshark (promisc is enabled on eth1)
sudo wireshark -i eth1 &

# Proxy a target's traffic through Burp: start Burp, set the target's
# browser / your tooling to use http://{{ lab_hosts.attacker }}:8080
burpsuite &
```

## Suggested learning path (OWASP-aligned)

1. **Recon** — nmap sweep, service/version detection, dir busting.
2. **Juice Shop** — walk the OWASP Top 10 challenges (broken auth, injection,
   XSS, SSRF). Proxy through Burp; watch requests in the SIEM.
3. **DVWA** — start at security level *low*, escalate to *medium*/*high* and
   re-run the same attacks to see the mitigations.
4. **Blue-team pivot** — open the SIEM viewer and search for your own attack
   traffic (`Failed password`, `sqlmap`, `nikto`) to learn detection.
